      <br>
      The most common dress code for Italian weddings is Cocktail, which means semi-formal attire, but with room for personalization.<br>
      <br>
      For example, men can wear a suit or a blazer paired with dress trousers. A colorful tie or bow tie adds a refined touch, though it&apos;s optional.
    </p>
